						               													<description>With each roll of the dice, move your piece through spaces outlining the major Jewish events in medieval Spain.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pull Explusion or Daily Life cards, as directed by the space you land on. These cards might cause you to be reincarnated (Gilgul space) as a different historical person (Nefesh/Soul cards) or put you in danger of excommunication (Herem space).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Along the way, those cards might also earn you tokens for: Torah (learning), Avodah (service), Gemilut Hasadim (showing kindness), and Emunah (faithfulness).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once you have collected 18 tokens (the same number as the Hebrew word for life), go to the 7th Heaven (Aravot) and pick a judgement (Din) card. Sometimes the King of Demons has tricked you into a lower heaven. But often your deeds are judged as Holy...and you WIN!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
